WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.230 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.230 --> 00:00:11.060 align:middle line:84%
When you're receiving
an incoming call,

00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:14.120 align:middle line:84%
a pop-up notification is
displayed on your screen.

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:16.070 align:middle line:84%
You can choose to
answer the call,

00:00:16.070 --> 00:00:18.440 align:middle line:84%
initiate a chat session
with that contact,

00:00:18.440 --> 00:00:20.330 align:middle line:90%
or decline the call.

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:23.760 align:middle line:84%
To answer the call,
select the Audio button.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.960 align:middle line:84%
When someone is
calling you with video,

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:28.200 align:middle line:84%
you can choose to answer
with video or answer

00:00:28.200 --> 00:00:30.150 align:middle line:90%
with audio only.

00:00:30.150 --> 00:00:33.330 align:middle line:84%
If you select to answer with
video, the camera on your PC

00:00:33.330 --> 00:00:37.030 align:middle line:84%
will turn on and the person
calling will see you.

00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:39.850 align:middle line:84%
To end an active call,
select the Hang Up icon

00:00:39.850 --> 00:00:44.280 align:middle line:84%
from either the communications
window or the main window,

00:00:44.280 --> 00:00:47.100 align:middle line:84%
or close the
communication window.

00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:49.860 align:middle line:84%
The system will ask you if
you'd like to end the call.

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.910 align:middle line:90%
Select End to end the call.

00:00:52.910 --> 00:00:59.968 align:middle line:90%